Brazilian Stock Movers: Bradesco, Santos Brasil and Usiminas

-- B y   N e y   H a y a s h i
-- 
2011-04-28T20:26:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/brazilian-stock-movers-bradesco-santos-brasil-and-usiminas.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Sao Paulo trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4:15 p.m. New York time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The Bovespa stock index fell 0.9 percent to 65,673.21.  Banco Bradesco SA (BBDC4)  (BBDC4 BS) tumbled 2.4 percent to 31.08
reais. Banco Espirito Santo SA,  Portugal ’s biggest publicly
traded bank by market value, agreed to sell a 2 billion-real
($1.27 billion) stake in the Brazilian bank.  Natura Cosmeticos SA (NATU3)  (NATU3 BS) dropped 3.4 percent to
43.25 reais.  Latin America ’s largest cosmetics company reported
first-quarter net income of 150.5 million reais, according to a
regulatory filing. The result was below the mean estimate of
161.8 million reais by eight analysts surveyed by Bloomberg.  Redecard SA (RDCD3)  (RDCD3 BS) jumped 6 percent to 23.90 reais. The
card-payment processor said in a filing it collected higher fees
in the first quarter. Figures eased concerns that increasing
competition would reduce profits, said Daniel Malheiros, an
analyst at Spinelli Corretora SA brokerage in Sao Paulo.  Santos Brasil Participacoes SA (STBP3)  (STBP11 BS) gained 2.2
percent to 29.85 reais. The port operator reported first-quarter
net profit of 43 million reais, from 4.8 million a year earlier,
according to a regulatory filing.  Usinas Siderurgicas de Minas Gerais SA (USIM5)  (USIM5 BS) tumbled 3
percent to 16.20 reais. Usiminas, as the steelmaker is known,
posted a first-quarter net loss of 26.1 million reais, compared
with revised profit of 365.3 million reais in the year-earlier
period, the company said today in a regulatory filing. It was
expected to post profit of 117.1 million reais on an adjusted
basis, according to the average of six analysts in a Bloomberg
survey.  To contact the reporter on this story:
